Given an integer x, return true if x is a palindrome, and false otherwise

So in this problem the logic used was to convert it in string and then compare the ith and (n-i-1)th value of the string.

Bool isPalindrome(intx){
If (x<0) return false;
string s = to_string(x);
int n = s.size();
for (int i=0;i<n/2;i++){
if (s[i] != s[n-i-1]){
return false;
}
}
return true;
}

